<section class="team">
  <div class="wrap-wide">
    <div class="team-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">The team</span>
      <h2>Who's <em>behind</em> it.</h2>
      <p>A small team — formulation scientists, athletes and operators — building IONIQ from a single warehouse in Brooklyn.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="team-grid">
      <div class="team-card">
        <div class="pic"><div class="ph"></div></div>
        <div class="body"><div class="role">Founder &amp; CEO</div><h4>Min-Jae Park</h4><p>Spent six years in Korean food-science research before starting IONIQ. The trip to the bamboo kilns was, in retrospect, inevitable.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="team-card">
        <div class="pic" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #B0B8A4, #97A78A);"><div class="ph"></div></div>
        <div class="body"><div class="role">Chief Scientific Officer</div><h4>Dr. Anya Mehta</h4><p>Exercise physiologist with a PhD in cellular hydration. Designed the formula and runs the clinical trials. Won't ship anything she can't defend on a paper.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="team-card">
        <div class="pic" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #D6EBDF, #B0B8A4);"><div class="ph"></div></div>
        <div class="body"><div class="role">Head of Sourcing</div><h4>Joren Cull</h4><p>Lives between Brooklyn and the Korean kilns. Has personally inspected every batch of bamboo salt that's shipped in an IONIQ sachet.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
